48static int
49nv50_fb_ram_new(struct nvkm_fb *base, struct nvkm_ram **pram)
50{
51 struct nv50_fb *fb = nv50_fb(base);
52 return fb->func->ram_new(&fb->base, pram);
53}
54
55static bool
56nv50_fb_memtype_valid(struct nvkm_fb *fb, u32 memtype)
57{
58 return nv50_fb_memtype[(memtype & 0xff00) >> 8] != 0;
59}

157static void
158nv50_fb_intr(struct nvkm_fb *base)
159{
160 struct nv50_fb *fb = nv50_fb(base);
161 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fb->base.subdev;
162 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
163 struct nvkm_fifo *fifo = device->fifo;
164 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
165 const struct nvkm_enum *en, *re, *cl, *sc;
166 u32 trap[6], idx, inst;
167 u8 st0, st1, st2, st3;
168 unsigned long flags;
169 int i;
170
171 idx = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100c90);
172 if (!(idx & 0x80000000))
173 return;
174 idx &= 0x00ffffff;
175
176 for (i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
177 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c90, idx | i << 24);
178 trap[i] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100c94);
179 }
180 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c90, idx | 0x80000000);
181
182 /* decode status bits into something more useful */
183 if (device->chipset < 0xa3 ||
184 device->chipset == 0xaa || device->chipset == 0xac) {
185 st0 = (trap[0] & 0x0000000f) >> 0;
186 st1 = (trap[0] & 0x000000f0) >> 4;
187 st2 = (trap[0] & 0x00000f00) >> 8;
188 st3 = (trap[0] & 0x0000f000) >> 12;
189 } else {
190 st0 = (trap[0] & 0x000000ff) >> 0;
191 st1 = (trap[0] & 0x0000ff00) >> 8;
192 st2 = (trap[0] & 0x00ff0000) >> 16;
193 st3 = (trap[0] & 0xff000000) >> 24;
194 }
195 inst = ((trap[2] << 16) | trap[1]) << 12;
196
197 en = nvkm_enum_find(vm_engine, st0);
198 re = nvkm_enum_find(vm_fault , st1);
199 cl = nvkm_enum_find(vm_client, st2);
200 if (cl && cl->data) sc = nvkm_enum_find(cl->data, st3);
201 else if (en && en->data) sc = nvkm_enum_find(en->data, st3);
202 else sc = NULL;
203
204 chan = nvkm_fifo_chan_inst(fifo, inst, &flags);
205 nvkm_error(subdev, "trapped %s at %02x%04x%04x on channel %d [%08x %s] "
206 "engine %02x [%s] client %02x [%s] "
207 "subclient %02x [%s] reason %08x [%s]\n",
208 (trap[5] & 0x00000100) ? "read" : "write",
209 trap[5] & 0xff, trap[4] & 0xffff, trap[3] & 0xffff,
210 chan ? chan->chid : -1, inst,
211 chan ? chan->object.client->name : "unknown",
212 st0, en ? en->name : "",
213 st2, cl ? cl->name : "", st3, sc ? sc->name : "",
214 st1, re ? re->name : "");
215 nvkm_fifo_chan_put(fifo, flags, &chan);
216}
217
218static void
219nv50_fb_init(struct nvkm_fb *base)
220{
221 struct nv50_fb *fb = nv50_fb(base);
222 struct nvkm_device *device = fb->base.subdev.device;
223
224 /* Not a clue what this is exactly. Without pointing it at a
225 * scratch page, VRAM->GART blits with M2MF (as in DDX DFS)
226 * cause IOMMU "read from address 0" errors (rh#561267)
227 */
228 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c08, fb->r100c08 >> 8);
229
230 /* This is needed to get meaningful information from 100c90
231 * on traps. No idea what these values mean exactly. */
232 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c90, fb->func->trap);
233}
234
235static void *
236nv50_fb_dtor(struct nvkm_fb *base)
237{
238 struct nv50_fb *fb = nv50_fb(base);
239 struct nvkm_device *device = fb->base.subdev.device;
240
241 if (fb->r100c08_page) {
242#ifdef __NetBSD__
243 const bus_dma_tag_t dmat = device->func->dma_tag(device);
244
245 bus_dmamap_unload(dmat, fb->r100c08_page);
246 bus_dmamem_unmap(dmat, fb->r100c08_kva, PAGE_SIZE);
247 bus_dmamap_destroy(dmat, fb->r100c08_page);
248 bus_dmamem_free(dmat, &fb->r100c08_seg, 1);
249 fb->r100c08_page = NULL;
250#else
251 dma_unmap_page(device->dev, fb->r100c08, PAGE_SIZE,
252 DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL);
253 __free_page(fb->r100c08_page);
254#endif
255 }
256
257 return fb;
258}
259
260static const struct nvkm_fb_func
261nv50_fb_ = {
262 .dtor = nv50_fb_dtor,
263 .init = nv50_fb_init,
264 .intr = nv50_fb_intr,
265 .ram_new = nv50_fb_ram_new,
266 .memtype_valid = nv50_fb_memtype_valid,
267};
268
269int
270nv50_fb_new_(const struct nv50_fb_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
271 int index, struct nvkm_fb **pfb)
272{
273 struct nv50_fb *fb;
274
275 if (!(fb = kzalloc(sizeof(*fb), GFP_KERNEL)))
276 return -ENOMEM;
277 nvkm_fb_ctor(&nv50_fb_, device, index, &fb->base);
278 fb->func = func;
279 *pfb = &fb->base;
280
281#ifdef __NetBSD__
282 {
283 const bus_dma_tag_t dmat = device->func->dma_tag(device);
284 int nsegs;
285 int ret;
286
287 fb->r100c08_page = NULL; /* paranoia */
288 fb->r100c08_kva = NULL;
289
290 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
291 ret = -bus_dmamem_alloc(dmat, PAGE_SIZE, PAGE_SIZE, 0,
292 &fb->r100c08_seg, 1, &nsegs, BUS_DMA_WAITOK);
293 if (ret)
294fail0: return ret;
295 KASSERT(nsegs == 1);
296
297 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
298 ret = -bus_dmamap_create(dmat, PAGE_SIZE, 1, PAGE_SIZE, 0,
299 BUS_DMA_WAITOK, &fb->r100c08_page);
300 if (ret) {
301fail1: bus_dmamem_free(dmat, &fb->r100c08_seg, 1);
302 goto fail0;
303 }
304
305 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
306 ret = -bus_dmamem_map(dmat, &fb->r100c08_seg, 1, PAGE_SIZE,
307 &fb->r100c08_kva, BUS_DMA_WAITOK);
308 if (ret) {
309fail2: bus_dmamap_destroy(dmat, fb->r100c08_page);
310 goto fail1;
311 }
312 (void)memset(fb->r100c08_kva, 0, PAGE_SIZE);
313
314 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
315 ret = -bus_dmamap_load(dmat, fb->r100c08_page, fb->r100c08_kva,
316 PAGE_SIZE, NULL, BUS_DMA_WAITOK);
317 if (ret) {
318fail3: __unused bus_dmamem_unmap(dmat, fb->r100c08_kva, PAGE_SIZE);
319 goto fail2;
320 }
321
322 fb->r100c08 = fb->r100c08_page->dm_segs[0].ds_addr;
323 }
324#else
325 fb->r100c08_page = alloc_page(GFP_KERNEL | __GFP_ZERO);
326 if (fb->r100c08_page) {
327 fb->r100c08 = dma_map_page(device->dev, fb->r100c08_page, 0,
328 PAGE_SIZE, DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL);
329 if (dma_mapping_error(device->dev, fb->r100c08))
330 return -EFAULT;
331 } else {
332 nvkm_warn(&fb->base.subdev, "failed 100c08 page alloc\n");
333 }
334#endif
335
336 return 0;
337}
338
339static const struct nv50_fb_func
340nv50_fb = {
341 .ram_new = nv50_ram_new,
342 .trap = 0x000707ff,
343};
344
345int
346nv50_fb_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_fb **pfb)
347{
348 return nv50_fb_new_(&nv50_fb, device, index, pfb);
349}
